The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Dec. 6: Trading in the bonus shares of Reliance Industries will start tomorrow. This is likely to swell the total number of shares of the company to as much as 330 crore. The company, which last month approved a 1:1 issue of bonus shares after a 12-year hiatus, had said it would issue a maximum of 166.97 crore equity shares of Rs 10 each as bonus to eligible shareholders.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 6: Indians who got the pink slip in the Gulf region following the Dubai debt crisis may look for some breather on their return to India with the Centre deciding to announce soon a special fund to rehabilitate overseas returnees who have lost jobs because of the economic downturn.                            
	 Melbourne, Dec. 6: Mining giants BHP Billiton and Rio Tinto have signed a $116 billion iron ore joint venture agreement to combine their western Australian iron ore operations. The agreement brings together two of the worlds three largest iron ore producers.                             
	 London, Dec. 6: Lakshmi Mittal will get a 1 billion windfall from a European scheme to curb global warming. His company ArcelorMittal, the worlds leading steel empire, will make the gain on carbon credits given to it under the European Emissions Trading Scheme.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 6: Private sector power producer JSW Energy has raised Rs 464.86 crore through the issue of shares to seven anchor investors under its public offer, which opens tomorrow for subscription.                                                                                                                          
